videos.headline: Bonnafon puts Louisville on the board
videos.description: Reggie Bonnafon scores the first touchdown of the game with an 18-yard run

videos.headline: Jackson gets into wrestling match with Kentucky defender
videos.description: Lamar Jackson runs for nine yards and is tackled on the sideline, where he gets into it with a Kentucky defender. Both players were accessed a personal foul penalty.

videos.headline: Williams punches it in for TD
videos.description: Dae Williams scores on a 1-yard touchdown run for Louisville.

videos.headline: Kentucky's Snell fights for TD
videos.description: Benny Snell Jr. powers through defenders to reach the end zone.

videos.headline: Louisville's Bonnafon takes option for TD
videos.description: Reggie Bonnafon scores an 11-yard touchdown off the option pitch from Lamar Jackson.

videos.headline: Jackson delivers perfect pass for 29-yard TD
videos.description: Lamar Jackson throws a dime to Dez Fitzpatrick along the sideline for a 29-yard Louisville touchdown.

videos.headline: Stoops says defense needs to improve
videos.description: Mark Stoops tells Olivia Harlan that his team needs to slow down Lamar Jackson and get some stops in the second half against Louisville.

videos.headline: Jackson scrambles, breaks tackles to pick up 1st down
videos.description: Lamar Jackson avoids the pass rush and jukes potential tacklers on his way to a first down.

videos.headline: Jackson fumbles snap, still picks up 1st down
videos.description: Lamar Jackson fumbles the snap in the end zone, recovers and still picks up a Louisville first down.

videos.headline: Jackson hits Smith for 14-yard TD
videos.description: Lamar Jackson throws to Jaylen Smith in the corner of the end zone to extend Louisville's lead

videos.headline: Kentucky's Snell pounds in for a score
videos.description: Benny Snell Jr. runs for his second touchdown of the game.

videos.headline: Petrino proud of his players after 44-17 win
videos.description: Bobby Petrino tells Olivia Harlan that he is proud of the way his players and coaches finished the season.

videos.headline: Jackson happy to have Governors Cup trophy back
videos.description: Lamar Jackson is happy with the way Louisville finished the season after a slow start.

videos.headline: Louisville defeats Kentucky 44-17
videos.description: Taylor Zarzour and Andre Ware break down Louiville's dominating win over rival Kentucky.
